text: Ochrosia tahitensis was a species of plant in the family Apocynaceae. The extinct plant species was endemic to Tahiti of the Society Islands, in French Polynesia. ==References== tahitensis Category:Flora of the Society Islands Category:Tahiti Category:Extinct flora of Oceania Category:Flora of French Polynesia Category:Plant extinctions since 1500 Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
